A Linux Distribution is an operating system made from a software collection that is based upon the linux kernel and a often package management system.
Linux OS -
       Linux Kernel
       GNU Shell ( GNU Not Unix) : this is the default shell on many operating system, when someone says GNU they usually means Bash.
       graphical desktop env
apt
A package management tool used to install, update, upgrade, and remove software.

sudo apt update       # Refresh package list
sudo apt upgrade      # Upgrade all installed packages
sudo apt install xyz  # Install a new package
apt
A package management tool used to install, update, upgrade, and remove software.
sudo
Runs the command with superuser (root) privileges — needed for system-level operations.
update
Updates the list of available packages and versions from online repositories.

It does NOT install or upgrade any actual packages — it just refreshes the local metadata.
